If you cross out prepositions, you will be able to quickly identify writing errors.

Prepositions and postpositions, together called adpositions, are a class of words used to express spatial or temporal relations or mark various semantic roles. A preposition or postposition typically combines with a noun phrase, this being called its complement,

![](data:image/png;base64,)

The two options are to cross out the preposition with pencil, or wrap them in parenthesis  
 

Errors that crossing out prepositions are helpful with:

Comparison errors, Singular-Plural Mismatches, idiom errors, parallelism errors, transition errors, and pronoun errors.
